<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+2020</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-2020</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>August 1, 2020</strong> - The winners in the <a href="/instagram-fan-art-contest">Instagram Fan Art Contest</a> have been chosen and published.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>February 8, 2020</strong> - The <a href="/scp-5000">SCP-5000</a> Contest is over! Congratulations to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(776854); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=776854&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609380041" alt="Tanhony" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=776854)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(776854); return false;">Tanhony</a></span> for winning the SCP-5000 slot!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>February 1, 2020</strong> - Check out <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/young-and-under-30">Underread and Underrated</a> for a deep dive into the hidden gems of SCP, complete with writing prompts and lore overviews!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+2019</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-2019</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>August 6, 2019</strong> - The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/collaboration-contest">Collab Contest</a> has closed. Congratulations to all who entered!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>May 6, 2019</strong> - Please see the following announcement regarding an ongoing license violation in Russia: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-11572837/announcement-regarding-ongoing-license-violation">Announcement Thread Here</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>April 23, 2019</strong> - Join #workshop on the synIRC network on May 5 at 1 PM EST for <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10752847/seminars-and-workshops">a seminar</a> on writing and creating dialogue!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>April 3, 2019</strong> - The winners of the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/144-hour-jam-contest">144-Hour Jam Contest</a> have been announced! Congratulations to everyone who participated! We had almost 140 entries, so go check them out! Also, don't forget to vote on your favorite <a href="http://scp-int.wikidot.com/international-goi-contest-2019">International Groups of Interest contest entries!</a></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>March 29, 2019</strong> - The <strong><a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/">Wanderers' Library</a></strong> has been relaunched with a brand-new look and a vision for the future! If you've ever enjoyed the Library but longed for it to be less ugly and more active, your dream has just come true. Join the <a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/system:real-time-chat">Library Chat</a> and read the <a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/orientation">Orientation</a> for more information.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>January 1, 2019</strong> - Happy New Year, Skippers! Welcome to 2019! In an effort to acknowledge and honor all of our hardworking reviewers, the <a href="/reviewers-spotlight-archive">Reviewers' Spotlight</a> will be replacing the previous &quot;Event Featured&quot; block. Big thanks to all of our talented critiquers who keep the forums running and the site flourishing!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+2018</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-2018</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>October 7, 2018</strong> - The international branches of the SCP community have teamed up to bring you a collection of translated SCPs from around the world! New articles are posted daily, and you can view them at the <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-international">International Branches Hub</a></strong>!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>August 17, 2018</strong> - The <a href="/scp4000contesthub">SCP-4000 Contest</a> is over! Be sure to check out all the entries! <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-series-5">Series V</a> is now open!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>July 12, 2018</strong> - <a href="/scpdeclassified">SCPDeclassified</a>, a <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCPDeclassified/">subreddit</a> devoted to literary analyses and plot explanations of SCP articles and concepts, recently reached 10,000 subscribers. Congratulations to them, and we look forward to reading their future declassifications!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>June 20, 2018</strong> - The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp4000contesthub">4000 Contest</a> is live! In honor of the site's 10th anniversary, the contest's theme is HISTORY! Here's to an epic contest and another ten years of SCP!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>May 21, 2018</strong> - The <strong><a href="http://scp-pt-br.wikidot.com/">Portuguese Branch</a></strong> is the newest member of the International SCP community! We wish them the best of luck and great success!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>May 5, 2018</strong> - Today marks the fifth anniversary of the <a href="http://lafundacionscp.wikidot.com/main">Spanish branch</a> of the wiki! Congratulations and here's to another five years of La Fundacion!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>April 2, 2018</strong> - Staff have started the process of migrating off of Wikidot, and we need <strong>your</strong> help. If you have professional experience in programming, quality assurance, marketing, law, finance, graphic design, or running a business or non-profit, and would be willing to donate your time and expertise, please sign up in the appropriate <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/forum/c-3335629/recruitment">Recruitment thread</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>April 1, 2018</strong> - April Fool's is over. We hope everyone had fun, and enjoyed our little <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-5663706/happy-april-fool-s">pranks and easter eggs</a>!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>March 11, 2018</strong> - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scpfmmdbc-hub">March Madness</a> returns (for real this time)! Get your predictions in now!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>February 2, 2018</strong> - THREE DAYS: That’s how long the next contest is! Join us for the first ever <a href="/72-hour-jam-contest">72-Hour Jam Contest</a> on February 17th!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
